headline: Opendoor (OPEN) Stock Trades Down, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of technology real estate company Opendoor (NASDAQ:OPEN) fell 4.3% in the afternoon session after the company decided to adjourn a special stockholder meeting scheduled to vote on a potential reverse stock split. The meeting, which was scheduled to address a proposal for a reverse stock split, was postponed until August 27, 2025.
